&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Coordinator/Band 7 AFC Salary/Progression opportunity for Senior Theatre Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Senior Theatre Practitioner with at least 2 years of band 6 experience looking to move into management or you are already working in a similar capacity and are looking for your next career move? If so, how would you like the opportunity to work in a developing organisation that is actively improving the coordination of our emergency, trauma and elective theatres. Experience within emergency and trauma theatres is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Walsall Manor has been awarded “Outstanding” by the Care Quality Commission (CQC) for care and is looking for individuals to join our team to actively contribute to our vision of being rated outstanding by 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will be responsible for the co-ordination of elective, emergency and trauma patients within the theatre environment ensuring that lists are as efficient and effective as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for patient’s journey and experience through the emergency and elective pathways and be a visible point of contact and support to theatre staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require multi-disciplinary working across the ward, support services and other members of the multi-disciplinary team to ensure optimum patient preparation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide a high level of skilled clinical care to all patients with support &amp; guidance to junior staff and be responsible for co-ordination of teaching and development of all grades of staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you meet the above criteria and want to develop your career within a forward thinking, patient focussed organisation we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLouisa AdamsJob titleClinical Theatre Services ManagerEmail addresslouisa.adams@walsallhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number07971 088880Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact Louisa Adams on extension 6861 or email louisa.adams@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
